+{"id":"bd-9iy8d","title":"Reject oversized btrfs dir/inode ref names during serialization","description":"Fresh-eyes btrfs serializer finding: BtrfsInodeRef::to_bytes and BtrfsDirItem::to_bytes encode name_len as u16 using unchecked casts. Names longer than u16::MAX silently truncate the on-disk length while appending the full name payload, producing malformed/corrupt payloads. Add fallible serializers, keep infallible helpers from silently truncating, and add regression coverage.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-27T08:16:07.035671905Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T08:21:16.839183224Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T08:21:16.837177474Z","close_reason":"Btrfs DIR_ITEM/INODE_REF serializers now have checked try_to_bytes APIs that reject oversized u16 name_len values, infallible to_bytes no longer silently truncates, and core btrfs directory mutation paths propagate checked serialization errors. Validation passed: focused ffs-btrfs regression, fmt, diff-check, UBS touched files, workspace check, and workspace clippy.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
