 {"id":"bd-9llzj","title":"[FUSE] FS_IOC_GETFSUUID ioctl — surface fs UUID via blkid-compatible API","description":"FS_IOC_GETFSUUID (0x40109409, _IOR(0x15, 0, struct fsuuid)) returns the 17-byte fsuuid struct: u8 fsu_len + u8 fsu_flags[2] + u8 fsu_uuid[16] (struct fsuuid from <linux/fsuuid.h>, kernel >= 6.5 / glibc commit 6f7c1e3). Used by blkid, util-linux libuuid, and systemd to identify the filesystem without reading the superblock directly. ext4 surfaces sb.uuid; btrfs surfaces sb.fsid. dispatch_ioctl currently has no handler -> ENOTTY. Acceptance: ioctl(fd, FS_IOC_GETFSUUID, &out) returns 17 bytes with fsu_len=16, fsu_flags zero, fsu_uuid matching the on-disk UUID. Read-side only; UUID is not user-settable.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:06:53.000423813Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:14:21.616277136Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:14:21.614338781Z","close_reason":"FS_IOC_GETFSUUID shipped via FsOps::fs_uuid + OpenFs override (ext4 sb.uuid / btrfs sb.fsid) + dispatch_ioctl branch + encode_fsuuid_response. 3 regressions cover encoded bytes, short-buffer EINVAL, and ext4 superblock-passthrough.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-9mdyg","title":"[FUSE] fallocate FALLOC_FL_INSERT_RANGE (shift right + insert hole)","description":"Follow-up to bd-ezmts: implement INSERT_RANGE = 0x20 in ext4_fallocate + a ffs_extent::insert_range helper (inverse of collapse_range).\n\nINSERT_RANGE shifts every extent past offset right by length and grows file size by length, leaving an unallocated hole in [offset, offset+length). Both must be block-aligned. ext4 reference: ext4_insert_range in fs/ext4/extents.c.\n\nImplementation sketch: ffs_extent::insert_range walks extents past the cut and re-inserts each at logical_block + count, then the caller bumps inode.size + nothing else (no allocation - the hole stays sparse until a write fills it).","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:03:33.784406005Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T11:10:19.773897767Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T11:10:19.771958425Z","close_reason":"FALLOC_FL_INSERT_RANGE shipped via ffs_extent::insert_range (split-straddler + descending-shift) + ext4_fallocate dispatch branch. 4 new ffs-core regressions cover tail shifts right + file grows + hole reads as zeros, unaligned EINVAL, at/past EOF EINVAL, INSERT_RANGE+KEEP_SIZE EINVAL.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}

